|-----|------|-------|--------------|----------|
| 1-2 | Pick one dependency source of truth; generate secondary files from it | — | CI check fails if any lockfile is out of sync | P1 |
| 2-3 | Align Python/package constraints across all apps | — | All `pyproject.toml` files use identical `requires-python` | P1 |
| 3-4 | Harden systemd units (non-root users, `NoNewPrivileges`, `ProtectSystem`) | — | `systemd-analyze security` passes for all 21 units | P0 |
| 3-4 | Move inline secrets out of service files into `/etc/aitbc/*.env` | — | `git grep -E "(AUTH_TOKEN|password|private_key)" -- "*.service"` == 0 | P0 |
| 4-5 | Make recovery service fail loudly (remove `|| true`) | — | Simulated failure → systemd reports `failed` | P1 |
| 4-5 | Add ShellCheck/shfmt to CI; fix flagged scripts | — | All `.sh` in `scripts/` pass ShellCheck | P1 |
| 5 | Add dry-run and confirmation modes to destructive operational scripts | — | `fuser -k` and `rm -rf` require `--yes` or `--dry-run` | P1 |
| 5 | Standardize observability (one telemetry stack) | — | Only one metrics/tracing module imported by each service | P1 |
| 5 | Lock down telemetry bind addresses (`0.0.0.0` → `127.0.0.1`) | — | CI grep for `0.0.0.0` in telemetry configs fails | P1 |
| 5 | Remove Docker claims from docs; add CI check against Docker files | — | `git ls-files | grep -E "(Dockerfile|docker-compose)"` == 0; docs state "systemd only" | P2 |

